Place is a circus, the walk in cooler is unorganized and never inspected. You have hot food with cold food, raw fish next to ground beef, beer sitting on top of food and vice versa, its never cleaned. Every single cook there is constantly drunk off company supply, doesn't matter if it is breakfast, lunch or dinner, they are drunk. Management plays favorites and let certain employees do whatever they want including drink. Everything is either bought frozen in bulk or made in bulk which allows food to spoil and bacteria to grow, such as the avocado rolls which are already bad by time people eat them(check for the black spotting on the tortillas and the dark color of the avocado). There are no recipes for the cooks to follow so never expect the same meal twice.  The quality of their products are definitely on the "bargain bin" side meaning you might get a premature chicken leg that's smaller than your pinky, or a chicken tender that is all bread, the likely hood of them being out of what you want is actually pretty high as well. My impression of the company is that they are closing soon and really just want to milk as much as they can out of their customers before they go.

I'm not sure why it took me so long to come here, but I'm glad I finally did!  Being a member of the American Homebrewers Association, I was presented with coupon for 15% off my bill at Weather Mark Tavern. Since it was a Saturday and I had a hankering for some brunch, I came here with some friends. We were surprised to find $15 bottomless mimosas!  So we all sat down in the comfy couches, which sectioned off by sails, and ordered mimosas and some food. I had the Classic Breakfast, which is 2 eggs, bacon or sausage, house potatoes, and toast. I got the sausage, which was really juicy and delicious.  We ended up staying until the mimosas ran out, at which point we finally left. I'm not even sure if I ended up even using my AHA discount, but we had a great time nonetheless!
